description: The American jobs market has been running in a much lower gear than previously thought, according to a preliminary report released Tuesday. author: CNN
description:
The American jobs market has been running in a much lower gear than previously thought, according to a preliminary report released Tuesday.

The US economy added about 911,000 fewer jobs than initially estimated for the year ending in March, the Bureau of Labor Statistics report suggests. If this were to hold – the final annual benchmark revision will be reported in February 2026 – it would be the largest annual revision to US jobs data on record.

CNN business and politics correspondent Vanessa Yurkevich reports. #CNN #News
title: Gigantic revision signals US job growth much weaker than believed

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said today that he won’t comment further on the letter inside Jeffrey Epstein’s “birthday book” allegedly bearing the president’s signature, telling NBC News it’s a “dead issue.”

“I don’t comment on something that’s a dead issue,” Trump said in a brief phone interview with the network this morning. “I gave all comments to the staff. It’s a dead issue.”

This is the first time Trump has been asked about the letter since it became public. Democrats on the House Oversight Committee posted an image of it on Monday after the panel obtained the letter through Epstein’s estate, though the Wall Street Journal reported on the letter’s existence and described its contents earlier in the summer.

Trump denies he wrote the letter, which also contains a drawing of the outline of a woman’s body and breasts. He sued the Journal for its initial reporting.

title: White House: Trump 'did not sign' Epstein birthday letter

The attack appears to be the first time Israel has launched an operation in Qatar. An Israeli official said the United States was told beforehand of the attack. CNN has reached out to the White House and the State Department for comment. The Qatari foreign ministry called the strike “cowardly,” saying it constitutes a “blatant violation of international laws and norms.”

CNN's Paula Hancocks reports from Abu Dhabi, Kevin Liptak reports from the White House and Clarissa Ward reports from London. #CNN #News
title: Qatar: Israel targeted residential buildings housing Hamas
